{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-1074"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Macaroni, Noodles, Couscous and Similar Farinaceous Products Coordination"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "1074"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :food/macaroni-noodles-couscous
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:food-security :food-safety :fair-labor]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :pasta-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies [:optimization :telemetry]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "PastaOpsAdvisor ⊣ Pasta Governor, langgraph-clj StateGraph
 (langgraph.graph, pastaops.operation/build), append-only audit ledger
 (pastaops.store/ledger + append-ledger!, MemStore). Fixes a prior
 deferred-stub gap (same compounding class as other cloud-itonami-isic-*
 siblings before their own fixes): `deps.edn` declared
 `io.github.kotoba-lang/langgraph` ONLY under the unused `:dev` alias's
 `:override-deps` with an EMPTY base `:deps` map (override-deps has
 nothing to override when the lib was never in the graph, so
 `langgraph.graph` was never actually resolvable on any real build/run/
 test path); `pastaops.advisor` was a docstring-only namespace with no
 protocol/implementation and was never `require`d by `pastaops.operation`
 -- there was no real Advisor node in any flow; and
 `pastaops.store/append-fact` (the ledger-append function) was called
 ONLY from test setup, never from any real commit/hold path, because
 there was no real commit/hold path (`run-operation` never touched a
 store). Now: a genuinely compiled StateGraph (`:intake -> :advise ->
 :govern -> :decide -+-> :commit / :request-approval -> :commit / :hold`)
 with `interrupt-before #{:request-approval}` + in-memory checkpointer
 for real human-in-the-loop resume, mirroring `bakeryops.operation`
 (cloud-itonami-isic-1071) node/edge structure. Four closed-allowlist ops
 (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-food-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. `:log-production-batch` / `:coordinate-shipment`
 (real actuation) and `:flag-food-safety-concern` (food-safety, never
 auto-resolved by confidence) ALWAYS escalate to a human plant operator
 via the compiled graph's `:request-approval` node (checkpoint-based
 resume), proven end-to-end by `test/pastaops/operation_graph_test.cljc`
 exercising commit / hard-hold (batch never staged, and a HARD
 drying-temp violation that pre-empts what would otherwise be an
 always-escalate op) / escalate-approve / escalate-reject / coordinate-
 shipment-unregistered-hold through the REAL compiled graph, including a
 falsifiable proof that a custom injected Advisor's own (randomly
 generated, non-hardcoded) proposal `:summary` is what lands in the
 committed ledger fact -- not a graph-internal literal. `pastaops.store`
 now also exposes a `Store` protocol (`MemStore`) alongside its original
 pure `{:batches ...}` value helpers (unchanged, still used directly by
 `pastaops.governor`'s independent checks). 47 tests / 173 assertions
 green (`clojure -M:dev:test`), clj-kondo 0 errors, demo runnable
 end-to-end (`clojure -M:dev:run`)."}
